<p><b>Radu Ştefan Mazăre</b> (born July 5, 1968) is a <a href="/wiki/Romania" title="Romania">Romanian</a> politician. His political activity began with his election to the <a href="/wiki/Chamber_of_Deputies_(Romania)" title="Chamber of Deputies (Romania)">lower house</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Parliament_of_Romania" title="Parliament of Romania">Parliament</a> on the <a href="/wiki/Democratic_Party_(Romania)" title="Democratic Party (Romania)">Democratic Party</a> list, which he left in 1997 to serve as an independent. In 2000 he defeated all party-supported contestants to be elected <a href="/wiki/Mayor" title="Mayor">mayor</a> of <a href="/wiki/Constan%C8%9Ba" title="Constanța">Constanța</a>, one of Romania's largest cities and its foremost seaport. Joining the <a href="/wiki/Social_Democratic_Party_(Romania)" title="Social Democratic Party (Romania)">Social Democratic Party</a> in 2003, he went on to win the following three elections with a comfortable majority. In 2015, during his fourth term, Mazăre resigned amid accusation of corruptions, citing the unbearable stress caused by what he claimed to be politically-motivated investigations.</p>
<p></p>
